41:10.581 --> 41:12.583
through flight school with him. And when we went to 
Vietnam, we were assigned to different

41:12.603 --> 41:16.727
squadrons.

41:18.226 --> 41:21.329
He really let it get to him. And during his year over 
there, he probably lost about 40 pounds by

41:21.350 --> 41:27.036
worrying about it. And he lived through it. I don't 
know how he is now. I haven't seen him since then.

41:33.583 --> 41:37.848
But he was an absolute nervous wreck. There are 
many, many tales, as you see on TV every now and

41:39.029 --> 41:43.875
then. They bring up another tale about Vietnam and 
all this, personal interviews and the like. where

41:48.280 --> 42:12.354
so many people have let things get to them, and 
blaming society and thinking that the US

41:48.280 --> 42:12.354
government and the US people owe them a life and a 
well-being for the rest of their days, which I

41:48.280 --> 42:12.354
totally disagree with. A person goes over there to 
do a job, And like, I would have been drafted, but I

42:19.330 --> 42:25.676
did volunteer. And anyone that's in any service 
besides the Army is a volunteer. And a lot of the

42:32.242 --> 42:34.405
ones in the Army are volunteers. And

42:36.507 --> 42:47.397
you're there to defend your country no matter what 
the politicians

42:48.845 --> 42:50.967
how bad they screwed up, or whatever. You're there 
to defend your country, you're there to do the job

42:51.388 --> 43:04.702
for your country, and you're laying your life on 
the line for yourself, your country, your kids,

42:51.388 --> 43:04.702
your family in the future. But did you ever 
question why you were doing what you were doing?

43:09.547 --> 43:16.354
Why they were making you do this?

43:16.840 --> 43:25.317
I never have been much of a person to be involved in 
politics and not that it would matter anyway. It

43:26.099 --> 43:37.161
would probably just have pissed me off even more to 
where maybe I would have been more adamant

43:26.099 --> 43:37.161
about the situation.

43:39.149 --> 43:41.031
Maybe it was just the way I was raised. You do your 
stint for your country, and you do the best you can.

43:45.977 --> 43:53.747
And if you lose a part of your body doing it, then 
that's the way it happens. Luckily, I didn't lose

43:55.229 --> 43:56.731
anything. I had a couple of holes in me, but I didn't 
lose anything. And I don't feel like... the U.S.

44:08.765 --> 44:14.591
government or the American people or society as a 
whole owes me a thing. I did my job, and that was it.

44:21.178 --> 44:35.312
Like I say, maybe it's the way I was raised, brought 
up, thankful to my mother and father that I could

44:21.178 --> 44:35.312
detach myself from the horror and tragedy that was 
going on over there. And I'll also credit some to

44:35.765 --> 44:40.431
the pilot that I was with. Not having, you know, I 
